{"TopicId":178489,"ForumId":29,"TopicTitle":"KSPEvent on unfocused, uncontrolled vessel","CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-09-23T16:55:00Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-09-23T16:55:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have the following event in a part module:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode prettyprint lang-html prettyprinted\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E [KSPEvent(name = \u0022Add\u0022, guiActive = true, guiActiveEditor = false, guiName = \u0022Add to current collection\u0022, guiActiveUncommand = true, requireFullControl = false, guiActiveUnfocused = true, unfocusedRange=100)]\n public void AddToCollection()\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m trying to make it available while focused on\u00A0another vessel.\u00A0 This can be a stand-alone part, it has a command module, but no ec, etc.\u00A0 Just a basic part.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis works when I focus onto it, but when focused on another vessel, it isn\u0027t showing up.\u00A0 I have to switch to the part/vessel in order to see it in the PAW\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAny ideas what I\u0027m doing wrong?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"fatcargo","CreatedById":93302,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-09-23T23:52:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes \u0022PAW\u0022 refer to \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/163711-141-paws-part-action-window-sorter-outer-1101-15032018/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EPart Action Window Sorter-Outer\u003C/a\u003E ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhile i tinkered with my code, i used following flags (this was done with stock part menus) \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E:\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode prettyprint lang-c prettyprinted\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003EguiActive \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E=\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022kwd\u0022\u003Etrue\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E\n\nguiActiveEditor \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E=\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022kwd\u0022\u003Etrue\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E\n\nexternalToEVAOnly \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E=\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022kwd\u0022\u003Efalse\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E\n\nguiActiveUnfocused \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E=\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022kwd\u0022\u003Etrue\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022com\u0022\u003E//this one ?\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E\n\nunfocusedRange \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E=\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022lit\u0022\u003E1\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022com\u0022\u003E//not directly relevant, though it wouldn\u0027t surprise me if KSP freaks out on large values\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThough i tested this by launching two probe cores separated with docking\u00A0 ports and batteries, then cheating them into orbit and then decoupling them. As distance grew, beyond 1m range,\u00A0 menu item for other vessel vanished. Note that distance is measured from part\u0027s stack attachment node (most likely first one in part.cfg, part i work with has only one).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-09-24T00:06:25Z\u0022 title=\u002209/24/2018 12:06  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 24, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by fatcargo\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003Ebetter explanation\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-09-24T01:29:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223456800\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022178489\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221537746732\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002293302\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022fatcargo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, fatcargo said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E \u0022PAW\u0022 refer\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E to \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/163711-141-paws-part-action-window-sorter-outer-1101-15032018/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EPart Action\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E Window Sorter-Outer\u003C/a\u003E \u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPAW = Part Action Window\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLooks like the\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre style=\u0022border:1px solid #888888;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;padding:2px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003EexternalToEVAOnly\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span